Blender 2.80 Release Candidate is available!
12 Jul @ 12:32pm - fsiddi
The (authority releases something) Co now been.



A Release Candidate is the final step before the release. Blender has been built and packaged just like how the official release would be, and is available for a short period of testing. Download via the Steam updater and give it a good try. If things go as expected, the final release will be one week after.

Blender 2.80 is a massive upgrade! Check out what's new on the Blender website[www.blender.org] and consider supporting development on fund.blender.org.

B updation version! Bugs still in software.
TH Nov, 28 @ 8 - FSIDDI


Today the Blender Foundation releases the first 2.80-beta version (a version of a piece of software that is made available for testing, typically by a limited number of users) which is better then previous one. No other release of Blende community. A couple of useful links:

  • The 5 top things you need to know about Blender 2.8
  • Blender 2.8 official page on https://www.blender.org/2-8/
  • The daily builds (download the beta[builder.blender.org])

Consider joining the Blender Development Fund[fund.blender.org] to support the project and make 2.80 the best release ever. Enjoy!

A beta version for Steam will come next month, after some initial testing. Stay tuned!
